   =20
      A nice gesture
   =20
 =20
Here is an article about campaign finance for local elections in New Jersey=
. Municipal contracting is hard=C2=A0because there are often =E2=80=9Cpay t=
o play=E2=80=9D rules forbidding firms from contributing to local officials=
=E2=80=99 election campaigns and also winning municipal contracts given out=
 by those officials. But those rules are complicated and there are exceptio=
ns, and so some firms will do business with a city while also contributing =
to the mayor=E2=80=99s campaign funds. And sometimes they will give reporte=
rs great quotes about it:In March 2020, Parsippany-based firm Statewide Str=
iping donated $2,600 to Fulop=E2=80=99s campaign; four months later, the ci=
ty (legally) awarded Statewide a $1.16 million contract for road painting.K=
enneth Kida, the president of Statewide, said such donations were meant as =
=E2=80=9Ca nice gesture.=E2=80=9D=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s just a thank you for=
 the pleasure of doing business with the city,=E2=80=9D he said.We  talk  e=
nough about these sorts of euphemisms that I wanted to make sure to record =
that one.=C2=A0
