olor: #ccc;"> working hard</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>Working in the office means experiencing the energy of a trading floor. On=
 her third day at JPMorgan=E2=80=99s office, 21-year-old environmental scie=
nce major Anna Albright learned how worked up traders can get.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It was June 16, and the Federal Reserve had just shock=
ed markets by signaling two potential interest-rate increases in 2023. The =
seventh floor of the largest U.S. bank was a flurry of chat pings, ringing =
phones and cross-floor shouting as analysts pored over Chair Jerome Powell=
=E2=80=99s press conference diction for an explanation behind the abrupt ch=
ange in the Fed=E2=80=99s dot plot.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=
=9CIt was like the Super Bowl, but way more intense,=E2=80=9D said Albright=
, a trading and sales summer analyst. =E2=80=9CWe were like =E2=80=98Oh my =
God, what world have we entered?=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And playing hard:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 1=
6px 0;">For others, New York=E2=80=99s reopening is an opportunity to bond =
with fellow interns after work. One popular spot is Phebe=E2=80=99s, the do=
wntown bar known as a =E2=80=9Chaven for NYU kids and Wall Street interns,=
=E2=80=9D according to bartender Lauren Ramirez, 28. It=E2=80=99s clear the=
 summer analysts have arrived when you see =E2=80=9Canything Vineyard Vines=
, pastel button-ups and boat shoes,=E2=80=9D Ramirez explained.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">By 10 p.m. on a Friday in June, interns crowded a pack=
ed dance floor, screaming along to an electronic remix of Taylor Swift=E2=
=80=99s =E2=80=9CLove Story,=E2=80=9D and the line to get in was the only t=
hing visible outside the entrance. By 10:15 p.m., the queue stretched down =
the street, crowding the sidewalk and blocking the entrance to neighboring =
apartments and businesses. Black cars double-parked to let out packs of you=
ng men and women as they headed inside and assumed a place at the bar.</p><=
/blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is nothing more intense than=
 the energy of a trading floor during a Fed press conference, unless it is =
the energy of Phebe=E2=80=99s on a summer Friday. I mean, I=E2=80=99m lying=
, there are totally=C2=A0things that are more intense than that, but the po=
int is that the Wall Street interns are having a nice time and learning a l=
ot about the industry and themselves.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"1=
